<div class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Design principles</h2>
  
  <div class="subsection">
    <h3 class="subsection-title">Typography guidelines</h3>
    
    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">✓ Use sentence case for headers</h4>
      <div class="principle-example good">
        <div class="example-text">Manage habits</div>
        <div class="example-text">Adding new habits</div>
        <div class="example-text">Set up next month</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Headers use sentence case for better readability and a more conversational, journal-like feel.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">✗ Avoid ALL CAPS text</h4>
      <div class="principle-example bad">
        <div class="example-text">MANAGE HABITS</div>
        <div class="example-text">ADDING NEW HABITS</div>
        <div class="example-text">SET UP NEXT MONTH</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-description">
        All caps text feels aggressive and breaks the calm, handwritten journal aesthetic. It also has accessibility issues.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">Typography hierarchy</h4>
      <div class="principle-example neutral">
        <div class="example-text" style="font-family: var(--font-caveat); font-size: var(--text-md);">Habit names (Caveat, 18px)</div>
        <div class="example-text" style="font-family: var(--font-caveat); font-size: var(--text-small); margin-top: var(--space-sm);">Mobile reflections (Caveat, 13px)</div>
        <div class="example-text" style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xxs); margin-top: var(--space-xs);">UI labels (Special Elite, 11px)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Two font families: Special Elite (typewriter) for UI, Caveat (script) for user content. Use opacity for hierarchy, not weight.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="subsection">
    <h3 class="subsection-title">Interface principles</h3>
    
    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">Japanese paper aesthetic</h4>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Clean washi paper background with organic dot grid. No decorative containers or gradients - let the content breathe.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">Hand-drawn variety</h4>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Each checkbox has unique hand-drawn variations (10 box styles, 10 X marks, 10 ink blots) for organic diversity.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">Tight vertical spacing</h4>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Zero gap between checkbox rows (--space-checkbox-gap: 0px) with minimal column gaps (--space-column-gap: 4px) for compact tracking.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="principle-item">
      <h4 class="principle-title">Design tokens only</h4>
      <div class="principle-description">
        Always use CSS custom properties from _design-tokens.scss. No hardcoded values for colors, spacing, or typography.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>